<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SHIFT CONTROL LINKAGE ADJUSTMENT PROCEDURE WITH MANUAL
        TRANSMISSION - MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1300102">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <para>At least once each year and in the event of clutch or transmission service, inspect the shift control
                linkage for worn or damaged parts. Worn parts could affect linkage adjustment and operation. When
                installing new parts the shift linkage should be lubricated and readjusted.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
